WEBVTT
NOTE OE3D — Script2 — English

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:01.484
Hello!

2
00:00:01.434 --> 00:00:05.222
You have just received your new prosthesis at Ortho Espace 3D.

3
00:00:05.222 --> 00:00:08.602
The first days are an important adaptation period.

4
00:00:08.602 --> 00:00:11.197
Here are our tips to get started well.

5
00:00:12.597 --> 00:00:14.221
Fitting the prosthesis.

6
00:00:14.171 --> 00:00:18.334
Start by putting the liner on your residual limb, ensuring there are no folds.

7
00:00:18.334 --> 00:00:20.664
Check that the skin is well tensioned.

8
00:00:20.664 --> 00:00:25.114
Then attach the prosthesis according to your device's attachment system.

9
00:00:26.514 --> 00:00:28.403
Building up wear time.

10
00:00:28.353 --> 00:00:31.594
Start with two hours per day and increase gradually.

11
00:00:31.594 --> 00:00:34.465
In the first week, aim for four to six hours.

12
00:00:34.465 --> 00:00:38.028
If pain appears, remove the prosthesis and contact us.

13
00:00:39.428 --> 00:00:41.119
The condition of your skin.

14
00:00:41.069 --> 00:00:44.512
After each wear, carefully inspect the entire residual limb.

15
00:00:44.512 --> 00:00:47.792
A slight redness that disappears in twenty minutes is normal.

16
00:00:47.792 --> 00:00:52.887
However, persistent redness, a wound or blisters require a consultation.

17
00:00:54.287 --> 00:00:55.974
Rehabilitation.

18
00:00:55.924 --> 00:00:59.791
Physical therapy is essential to regain your independence.

19
00:00:59.791 --> 00:01:03.986
Work on balance, walking and muscle strengthening at your own pace.

20
00:01:03.986 --> 00:01:07.492
Our team at Ortho Espace 3D coordinates your follow-up.

21
00:01:08.892 --> 00:01:12.433
Our practitioners are available to answer all your questions.

22
00:01:12.383 --> 00:01:16.135
Do not hesitate to call us or send us a message on WhatsApp.

23
00:01:16.135 --> 00:01:18.411
Courage — you are not alone!
